Hello, you can do so by creating a repository and grouping each exercises by the part and name of excercise for instance your repo structure could look like:

```
|-- part0
|-- part1
|   |-- anecdotes
|   |-- courseinfo
|   `-- unicafe
|-- part2
|   |-- countries-data
|   |-- courseinfo
|   `-- phonebook
|-- part3
|   |-- phonebook-frontend
|   `-- phonebook-backend
|-- part4
|   `-- bloglist
|-- part5
|   |-- bloglist-backend
|   |-- bloglist-frontend
|   |-- node_modules
|   |-- playwright-report
|   |-- test-results
|   `-- tests
|-- part6
|   |-- anecdotes-query
|   |-- anecdotes-redux
|   `-- unicafe-redux
|-- part7
|   |-- bloglist-extended
|   |-- country-hook
|   |-- routed-anecdotes
|   `-- ultimate-hooks
|-- part8
|   |-- library-frontend
|   `-- library-backend
`-- part9
    |-- WebExercises
    |-- courseinfo-ts
    |-- flight-diary
    `-- patientor
``` 

The first 9 parts can be in the same repo, but you should create seperate repos from part 10 - 13 

In the github url field of the submission form you can copy the URL of the repo e.g github.com/<username>/fullstackopen. (Not the URL of individual parts)